# Debug the container

The debug container image includes [debugpy], allowing you to attach a remote
debugger to the running process.

## Pull the debug image

```bash
docker pull ghcr.io/{{ repository_namespace }}/{{ repository_name }}:latest-debug
```

## Run the debug container

```bash
docker run -it --rm \
    -p 5678:5678 \
    ghcr.io/{{ repository_namespace }}/{{ repository_name }}:latest-debug \
    -m {{ package_name }}
```

The container starts [debugpy] listening on port 5678 and waits for a debugger
to connect before executing `{{ package_name }}`.

## Attach VSCode

Add this configuration to `.vscode/launch.json`:

```json
{
    "version": "0.2.0",
    "configurations": [
        {
            "name": "Attach to container (debugpy)",
            "type": "debugpy",
            "request": "attach",
            "connect": {
                "host": "localhost",
                "port": 5678
            },
            "pathMappings": [
                {
                    "localRoot": "${workspaceFolder}/src",
                    "remoteRoot": "/app/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
```

Press **F5** or use **Run → Start Debugging** to connect. The container resumes
execution once the debugger attaches.

[debugpy]: https://github.com/microsoft/debugpy
